# Hackathon Notebooks – Implementation Plan (v2)

Two Jupyter notebooks for a pharmacogenomics hackathon, runnable on students' **local machines**.

---

## Key Design Decisions (from feedback)

1. **ssGSEA IDs** – same patients as other modalities → merge directly on `Patient_ID` (no harmonization needed)
2. **NE patients** – dropped with an explanatory comment (not evaluable for RECIST)
3. **Preprocessing flow** – §4/§5/§6 merged into **one integrated section**: each step gets introduction → description → code block
4. **Train/Test split** – All 5 modalities merged on `Patient_ID` → 80:20 stratified split → training set for Notebook 1, test set for Notebook 2
5. **Deployment flow** – Students load saved model + artifacts, apply to held-out test modalities, submit predictions via Google Form

---

## Proposed Changes

### [NEW] [01_Model_Development.ipynb](file:///Users/thechuongtrinh/Workspace/Hackathon_DIGPHAT/01_Model_Development.ipynb)

| Section | Content |
|---------|---------|
| **Header** | Title, hackathon context, imports |
| **§1 Objective** | Clinical question (ccRCC + ICB + RECIST), target population |
| **§2 Dataset Overview** | Load & display all 5 modalities `.head()`, cohort description, `missingno` heatmap |
| **§2 Data Integration** | Merge all modalities on `Patient_ID`, 80:20 stratified split → save `test_data.csv` for deployment |
| **§3 Outcome** | RECIST binary mapping (CR/PR/CRPR→1, SD/PD→0, **drop NE with comment**), class imbalance bar chart |
| **§4 Data Processing** | Integrated flow: RNA-seq (gene conversion mention, TPM noted, low-expr filter, scale) → Mutations (binary encode, NO_IF→NaN) → Deconv (log-transform) → Pathways (scale) → Clinical (encode + standardize) → Missing values (missingno + MICE) → Feature selection (variance, L1/ElasticNet) → PCA on transcriptome |
| **§5 Models** | Stratified K-Fold CV: LogReg, Decision Tree, RF, SVM, XGBoost, MLP |
| **§6 Evaluation** | PR AUC, balanced accuracy, F1, MCC, confusion matrix, learning curves |
| **§7 Improvements** | SMOTE, hyperparameter tuning ideas |
| **§8 Interpretation** | Feature importance plots |
| **Save** | `joblib.dump` model, scaler, selected features → `artifacts/` |

---

### [NEW] [02_Model_Deployment.ipynb](file:///Users/thechuongtrinh/Workspace/Hackathon_DIGPHAT/02_Model_Deployment.ipynb)

| Section | Content |
|---------|---------|
| **Load artifacts** | `joblib.load` model, scaler, feature list from `artifacts/` |
| **Load test data** | Load the held-out test modalities saved from Notebook 1 |
| **Apply preprocessing** | Align features, apply stored transforms |
| **Predict** | Generate probabilities + binary predictions |
| **Report** | Template metrics (when labels available): ROC AUC, PR AUC, MCC, confusion matrix |
| **Submit** | `requests.post` to Google Form (placeholder entry IDs) |

---

